 Simphiwe Nkosi and Zanele Vilakazi along with other police officers were arrested on June 21. The arrest was spear-headed by the Hawks Serious Corruption Unit and the National Traffic Anti-Corruption Unit, during their ‘Operation Take-Down’.
A total of seven law enforcers were arrested. Also read: Five officers arrested during ‘Operation Take-Down’ It is alleged the suspects solicited bribes from the motorists on the N4, between Komatipoort and Middelburg. Khethiwe Mkhabela, Lucky Mabena, both traffic officials, and David Mahlare Ntuli a police officer, was also arrested in Malelane and appeared before the Komatipoort Magistrate Court on Friday. Also read: Middelburg police officer arrested during Hawks operation They were granted R1000 bail each. Nkosi and Vilakazi were also granted R1000 bail, the matter will appear before the court in July.     Four killed after minibus and truck collide on N11 near Doornkop Elderly lady escapes with her life Parkrun fever breaks out Military troop imposter arrested • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za